'''Isidro Miguel Pitta Saldivar'''<ref name="auto">{{Cite web | url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/2020/08/02/isidro-pitta-en-la-mira/ | title=Isidro Pitta, en la mira - Fútbol - ABC Color | access-date=2020-11-06 | archive-date=2020-08-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814002451/https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/2020/08/02/isidro-pitta-en-la-mira/ | url-status=live }}</ref> (born 14 August 1999)<ref name="auto2">{{Cite web | url=http://www.cronica.com.py/2019/07/18/me-llaman-olimpia/ | title=Crónica / "Si me llaman de Olimpia..." | date=18 July 2019 | access-date=6 November 2020 | archive-date=16 May 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516070855/http://www.cronica.com.py/2019/07/18/me-llaman-olimpia/ | url-status=live }}</ref> is a [[Paraguay]]an [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Red Bull Bragantino]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Asunción]], Pitta was formed at the [[Cerro Porteño]] youth academy from 2014 to 2017, where he was leading goal scorer for its teams.<ref name="auto1">[https://www.m.d10.ultimahora.com/isidro-pitta-y-el-debut-sonado-un-goleador-pasado-azulgrana-n2808378.html/amp Unknown]{{Dead link|date=February 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> His playing style at Cerro Porteño was an area-man.<ref name="auto3">{{Cite web | url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/isidro-pitta-vikingo-paraguayo-quiere-independiente-incertidumbre-aleja-argentina_0_BHUvQM2vk.html | title=Isidro Pitta, el Vikingo paraguayo que quiere Independiente pero al que la incertidumbre lo aleja de la Argentina | date=4 September 2020 | access-date=1 December 2020 | archive-date=25 October 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025220012/https://www.clarin.com/deportes/isidro-pitta-vikingo-paraguayo-quiere-independiente-incertidumbre-aleja-argentina_0_BHUvQM2vk.amp.html | url-status=live }}</ref>

===Alvarenga===
Pitta briefly played for [[Portugal|Portuguese]] club [[G.D. Santa Cruz de Alvarenga|Alvarenga]] in [[Arouca, Portugal|Arouca]] for six months during the 2017–18 season,<ref name="auto2"/> where he scored 5 goals in 14 matches. Upon returning to Paraguay from Portugal, Pitta trialed for Primera División Paraguaya club [[Club Guaraní|Guaraní]].<ref name="auto"/>

===Deportivo Santani===
In 2019, Pitta signed a two-year contract with Deportivo Santaní.<ref name="auto1"/> Whilst at Deportivo Santani, Pitta was represented by Juan Dragotto.<ref name="auto4">{{Cite web | url=https://versus.lanacion.com.py/versus/2019/06/08/todos-lo-quieren-a-isidro-pitta/ | title=Todos lo quieren a Isidro Pitta | date=8 June 2019 | access-date=8 November 2020 | archive-date=19 April 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230419043158/https://versus.lanacion.com.py/versus/2019/06/08/todos-lo-quieren-a-isidro-pitta/ | url-status=live }}</ref>

In March 2019, Pitta debuted and scored in the same game for Deportivo Santaní against Olimpia Asunción. He entered the pitch at the 13th minute of the first half, then scored his goal in the second half of a game which ended in a 2–2 draw.<ref name="auto1"/>

Amongst other clubs in Paraguay, [[Argentina]] and [[Chile]], [[Club Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]] were interested in Pitta during 2019.<ref name="auto4"/>

In December 2019, Paraguayan Periodic [[List of newspapers in Paraguay|HOY]] announced that Pitta would join [[Sportivo Luqueño]] for the 2020 season and had departed Deportivo Santani, who descended to the country's second-tier.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.hoy.com.py/deportes/deja-santani-y-se-integra-al-sportivo-luqueno/amp | title=Diario HOY &#124; Amparados bajo la bendición de la Cruz | date=26 April 2016 | access-date=8 November 2020 | archive-date=2 October 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211002120101/https://www.hoy.com.py/deportes/deja-santani-y-se-integra-al-sportivo-luqueno/amp | url-status=live }}</ref>

===Sportivo Luqueño===
In August 2020, Pitta was in the interest of [[Argentina|Argentine]] club [[Union de Santa Fé]] after scoring three goals in three games following the recommencement of the 2020 season.<ref name="auto"/> In September 2020, Tigo Sports announced that Pitta was in the orbit of [[Primera División Argentina]] club [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/isidro-pitta-aparece-en-la-orbita-de-independiente-de-argentina | title=Tigo Sports Paraguay | access-date=2020-11-07 | archive-date=2020-11-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113115549/http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/isidro-pitta-aparece-en-la-orbita-de-independiente-de-argentina | url-status=live }}</ref> Independiente unsuccessfully submitted a loan offer for Pitta with an option to buy him.<ref name="auto3"/>

===Olimpia===
In September 2020, Pitta joined [[Club Olimpia]] of [[Asunción]] from [[Sportivo Luqueño]] for the remainder of the 2020 season and the [[2020 Copa Libertadores]] group stage. Prior to the transfer, Pitta had scored 8 goals and created 4 assists in 18 league games for Sportivo Luqueño during the [[2020 Paraguayan Primera División season|2020 season]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/olimpia-le-da-la-bienvenida-a-isidro-pitta | title=Tigo Sports Paraguay | access-date=2020-09-17 | archive-date=2020-10-31 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031063918/http://www.tigosports.com.py/futbol/olimpia-le-da-la-bienvenida-a-isidro-pitta | url-status=live }}</ref>

===Huesca===
On 16 August 2021, Pitta moved to Spain and signed a four-year contract with [[Segunda División]] side [[SD Huesca]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sdhuesca.es/noticia/isidro-pitta-un-delantero-referencia-para-la-sd-huesca|title=Isidro Pitta, un delantero referencia para la SD Huesca|trans-title=Isidro Pitta, a target man for SD Huesca|publisher=SD Huesca|language=es|date=16 August 2021|accessdate=16 August 2021|archive-date=25 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211025220013/https://www.sdhuesca.es/noticia/isidro-pitta-un-delantero-referencia-para-la-sd-huesca|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goals abroad on 24 September, netting a brace in a 2–0 away win over [[Real Sociedad B]].

====Loan to Juventude====
[[File:Brasileirão A- Corinthians 2 x 0 Juventude - Isidro Pitta.jpg|thumb|right|180px|Pitta playing for [[Esporte Clube Juventude|Juventude]] in 2022]]
On 28 January 2022, Pitta switched teams and countries again after signing a one-year loan deal with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] side [[Esporte Clube Juventude|Juventude]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sdhuesca.es/noticia/isidro-pitta-jugara-cedido-en-el-esporte-clube-juventude-de-brasil|title=Isidro Pitta jugará cedido en el Esporte Clube Juventude de Brasil|trans-title=Isidro Pitta will play on loan at Esporte Clube Juventude from Brazil|publisher=SD Huesca|language=es|date=28 January 2022|accessdate=28 January 2022|archive-date=28 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128213811/https://www.sdhuesca.es/noticia/isidro-pitta-jugara-cedido-en-el-esporte-clube-juventude-de-brasil|url-status=live}}</ref> He has been a regular starter for the club, but his team was relegated at the end of the [[2022 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|season]].

===Cuiabá===
On 21 December 2022, Pitta signed a four-year contract with [[Cuiabá Esporte Clube|Cuiabá]], another [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cuiabaesporteclube.com.br/pitta-e-do-dourado/|title=Pitta é do Dourado|trans-title=Pitta is from ''Dourado''|publisher=Cuiabá EC|language=pt-BR|date=21 December 2022|accessdate=31 December 2022|archive-date=31 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231182156/http://cuiabaesporteclube.com.br/pitta-e-do-dourado/|url-status=live}}</ref>

==International career==
Pitta made his debut for the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]] on 6 September 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against Uruguay at the [[Estadio Centenario]]. He started the game and played 61 minutes, as the game ended with the score of 0–0.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/684612/paraguay-uruguay|title=Uruguay v Paraguay game report|date=6 September 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pitta's appearance is likened to [[Ragnar Lodbrok]] from the successful series [[Vikings (2013 TV series)|Vikings]]. He is nicknamed ''Viking'' and he celebrates his goals with the same celebration as [[Conor McGregor]].<ref name="auto3"/>

